                    "SS2_EXECUTIONER_PASSIVE_NAME":  "BaÃ±o de Sangre",
                    "SS2_ITEM_DROIDHEAD_LORE":  "Pedido: Security Robot\nTracking Number: 1138***\nEstimated Delivery: 5/14/2056\nForma de envÃ­o: Priority / Fragile\nDirecciÃ³n de envÃ­o: RaCom Robotics, Asimov, Mars\nDetalles de envÃ­o:\n\nThis was one of the few complete bits we could salvage from those stolen security robots... That militant group on Pluto had stolen a bunch of those ER-14s, and had been using \u0027em at their bases for a while. This one specifically, ER-14XPC5VVUFF, lines up with the ones you\u0027d tried to recall a while back. I don\u0027t know this history, I just know there was a big bounty for whoever could find the remains for this batch. There\u0027s other remnants, too, but they\u0027re much less complete... Shouldn\u0027t be any danger anymore, at least. Gimme a heads up if you want those shipped your way, too.\n",
