                    "SS2_ACHIEVEMENT_CHIRR_HEADBUTT_NAME":  "Chirr: Long Live the Queen",
                    "SS2_EQUIP_BACKTHRUSTER_LORE":  "\u003cstyle=cMono\u003eTranscripciÃ³n de audio completa de ecos de seÃ±al. Asignando tokens genÃ©ricos.\u003c/style\u003e\n\nHOMBRE 1: Esta es una idea terrible, Â¿sabes?\n[metal traqueteando]\n\nHOMBRE 2: Dices eso de cada idea que tengo.\n\nHOMBRE 1: Porque todas tus ideas son terribles.\n\n[motor chisporroteando]\n\nHOMBRE 2: Rrgh, oh, Â¡vamos, entonces! Funcionabas bien hace un minuto.\n\nHOMBRE 1: QuizÃ¡s sabe que estÃ¡ atado a tu espalda, y no a un trozo de carga.\n\nHOMBRE 2: Â¡Oh, buen punto! Apuesto a que tienen un seguro de algÃºn tipo... Ah, ahÃ­ estÃ¡.\n\n[clic]\n\nHOMBRE 1: Yo... No deberÃ­a haber dicho nada.\n\nHOMBRE 2: Nah, Â¡esto es genial! Bien, cuenta atrÃ¡s.\n\nHOMBRE 1: Ugh... Bien. Tres-\n\n[propulsor despegando]\n\n\u003cstyle=cMono\u003eFin de la transcripciÃ³n solicitada.\u003c/style\u003e",
                    "SS2_DRONE_SHOCK_NAME":  "Dron de Descarga",
                    "SS2_ITEM_NEEDLES_LORE":  "\u003cstyle=cMono\u003eUES Informe de incidente de entrega ID 219560163 encontrado.\n\nReproduciendo...\u003c/style\u003e\n\n\"El personal de entrega Will Stetson, nÃºmero 604, fue admitido en la bahÃ­a mÃ©dica a bordo del UES [REDACTED], hace aproximadamente 22 horas, debido a complicaciones relacionadas con el manejo aberrante comportamiento del paquete.\n\nMientras hacÃ­a sus rondas, Will notÃ³ que uno de los cofres golpeÃ³ repentinamente, bastante fuerte, detrÃ¡s de Ã©l. Preocupado de que alguien pudiera haber intentado enviar un animal vivo bajo el protocolo estÃ¡ndar, sintiÃ³ la necesidad de investigar. En cambio, lo que habÃ­a en el cofre era un pequeÃ±o paquete de plÃ¡stico que contenÃ­a una gran cantidad de agujas de coser particularmente grandes, obviamente empaquetadas demasiado apretadas para cualquier cantidad. safety.\n\nFinalmente, y probablemente en un error de juicio, Will decidiÃ³ tocar el paquete. Esto provocÃ³ que el paquete se rompiera repentinamente en su direcciÃ³n general, dejando su parte frontal superior cubierta de cortes profundos. Tiene suerte de que alguien lo encontrÃ³ rÃ¡pidamente. Parece estar bien, pero se estarÃ¡ recuperando del shock y la pÃ©rdida de sangre por un tiempo. \"\n\nEn.",
                    "SS2_ITEM_COFFEEBAG_NAME":  "Bolsa de CafÃ©",
                    "SS2_NEMCOMMANDO_LORE":  "He lays to rest by a fire, setting the weapons he carries within an arm\u0027s reach. Checking his surroundings, hoping the cave he hid in would be enough shelter. Some would say, it isn\u0027t wise to be overly cautious. He would say, \u003ccolor=#FFCCED\u003ethey haven\u0027t seen enough.\u003c/color\u003e\n\nThe service pistol he got when he enlisted. Well used, dirtied, and loved. It\u0027s brought him through thick and thin, no matter which mission he took on. Some would say, only a fool would trust their weapon. He would say, \u003ccolor=#FFCCED\u003eyour weapon is all you can trust.\u003c/color\u003e\n\nThe blade of a fallen brother of war. Picked from what he could scavenge of the last of humanity he\u0027s seen. Some would say, it keeps their spirits united. He would say, \u003ccolor=#FFCCED\u003eit\u0027s to keep their spirits from joining for as long as possible.\u003c/color\u003e\n\nThe loads of cargo that landed with him. Each item picked from a chest, keeping him alive in one way or another. Dozens of shipments to anyone but him. Some would say, they aren\u0027t his items to take. He would say, \u003ccolor=#FFCCED\u003eif he doesn\u0027t take them, then no one will.\u003c/color\u003e\n\nThe glow of a violet light coming from deeper within the cave. Calming, warming... beckoning. Welcoming him deeper and deeper, promising safety. Some would say, what sounds too good to be true probably is. He would say, \u003ccolor=#FFCCED\u003eFaust was a wise man.\u003c/color\u003e",
                    "SS2_KNIGHT_UTILITY_LEAP_DESC":  "Corre hacia adelante, gira y corta repetidamente para \u003cstyle=cIsDamage\u003e120% de daÃ±o\u003c/style\u003e por golpe. El nÃºmero de golpes aumenta con la velocidad de ataque.",
                    "SS2_PLAYER_DAMAGE_25_DECREASE_BODY_TOKEN":  "Los jugadores infligen 75% de daÃ±o.",
                    "SS2_LAMP_BODY_NAME":  "Seguido",
                    "SS2_NEMHUNTRESS2_DESCRIPTION":  "La Cazadora NÃ©mesis ataca lenta pero despiadadamente con su letal arco largo y hacha doble.",
                    "SS2_CHIRR_DETONATE_DESCRIPTION":  "\u003cstyle=cIsUtility\u003eReemplaza Especial\u003c/style\u003e. Haz explotar a tu amigo por \u003cstyle=cIsDamage\u003e1000-4000% de daÃ±o\u003c/style\u003e.",
                    "SS2_ITEM_MOLTENCOIN_LORE":  "Pedido: Molten Coin\nTracking Number: 446*****\nEstimated Delivery: 09/22/2056\nForma de envÃ­o: Standard\nDirecciÃ³n de envÃ­o: Venetian Police Department, Brithen, Venus\nDetalles de envÃ­o:\n\nHey, I found another piece of evidence relating to that bombing at Parathan Square a couple days ago.\n\nSo, you know how the investigators had to postpone their analysis because the area was way too hot? Well, the space finally cooled off this morning, and I managed to find this melted coin stuck to the pavement. A quick chemical test says it\u0027s probably made mostly of tungsten with a gold coating, and it also hasn\u0027t cooled off since I peeled it off the ground.\n\nI\u0027m not really sure what it could mean, though. Maybe a good luck charm, or a calling card? Either way, I\u0027m sending it to you, since, quite frankly, you need all the help you can get. I mean, 7 people dead, 18 injured, nearly half a million in property damages, and all you\u0027ve got for evidence is a melted coin and a blown-up cafe? Well, you\u0027ve got my sympathy, man. Good luck on the case.\n",
                    "SS2_ACHIEVEMENT_STICKYOVERLOADER_NAME":  "Overloaded",
